        '',
        'I was scared of stigma. I had heard people use "bipolar" as an insult. I did not want to be that to my classmates.',
        '',
        'I had 504 plan. Mental health-related accommodations. Counselor knew. Case manager knew. No one else.',
        '',
        'In college I started telling close friends. Most surprised me with kindness. One did not. That friend faded out.',
