        '',
        'People came up to me for weeks. Some had bipolar too. Some had family with mental illness. Some just wanted to thank me.',
        '',
        'I work in mental health now. I write about my life. I am open about my diagnosis. Not as definition, as one part.',
        '',
        'What I tell younger people with serious mental health diagnosis: You get to choose disclosure. Each person, each time. Some people earn it. Some never will. AND, when you do disclose, you may find solidarity you did not expect.'
